The paper focuses on image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel active learning framework, which involves updating the feature representation and classifier with progressively annotated informative samples, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions face recognition and object categorization, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
